						               													<description>&amp;#230;&amp;#156;&amp;#173;&amp;#230;&amp;#157;&amp;#159;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#168;&amp;#230;&amp;#186;&amp;#182;&amp;#233;&amp;#137;&amp;#177;&amp;#231;&amp;#130;&amp;#137; (Satsutaba to Youkouro) is a 2 player bluffing card game from Japan. The players take two roles; one is building a road and the other is building on the road side. The designer likens the game to Skull. The game title translates as &amp;quot;Bankrolls and Blast Furnaces&amp;quot;. The player who most recently fell into a blast furnace gets to go first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player arranges five good tiles (bankrolls) and one bad tile (a blast furnace) in a face-down line. The other player turns them over from left to right until they want to stop.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The turning player gets a point for each good tile they turned over, a bonus two points if they stopped just before the bad tile, and no points at all if they turned over the bad tile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The placing player gets a point for each good tile they placed before the bad tile (i.e. each one that the turning player had an opportunity to take), plus a bonus two points if the turning player turned over the bad tile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Swap places and do it again, do all of that three times with double points in the last round, whoever has the most points wins.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
